    • Uses of INavigation in parkingRobot.hsamr0

      Classes in parkingRobot.hsamr0 that implement INavigation 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  NavigationAT
      A executable basic example implementation of the corresponding interface provided by the Institute of Automation with limited functionality: In this example only the both encoder sensors from the IPerception implementation are used for periodically calculating the robots position and corresponding heading angle (together called 'pose').

      Constructor and Description
      ControlRST(IPerception perception, INavigation navigation, NXTMotor leftMotor, NXTMotor rightMotor)
      provides the reference transfer so that the class knows its corresponding navigation object (to obtain the current position of the car from) and starts the control thread.
      HmiPLT(IPerception perception, INavigation navigation, IControl control)
      Creates a new HmiPlt module.
